<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Direct-sale (LemonSqueezy / website-download) variant of
      Splynek's entitlements.  Used for the 2026-06 launch outside
      the Mac App Store while Apple's v1.0 MAS re-review queue
      stays stalled past day 30.  See LAUNCH-WITHOUT-APPLE.md at
      the repo root for the strategy doc.

      Identical in capability to Resources/Splynek.entitlements
      (the existing Developer-ID DMG variant): sandboxed,
      hardened-runtime-friendly, no iCloud.  This file exists as a
      distinct named target so the launch build path is explicit:

        SIGN_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: …" \
        ENTITLEMENTS="Resources/Splynek-DirectSale.entitlements" \
          ./Scripts/build.sh release

      …and so when MAS clears, the parallel-MAS build picks
      Splynek-MAS.entitlements without ambiguity.

      Sandbox stays enabled — it's a good security posture for a
      download manager and lets us keep the same hardened runtime
      gates that protect the existing v0.x DMG users.  Sparkle 2.x
      auto-update works inside this sandbox via its
      `XPCInstallerService` path; no extra entitlements needed.

      License file double-click activation works via the
      `.splynekkey` file association declared in Resources/Info.plist
      (CFBundleDocumentTypes).  When the user opens a license file,
      macOS routes it to Splynek.app via the standard
      `application(_:open:)` path; we verify the Ed25519 signature
      against the public key embedded at build time, then store the
      license in ~/Library/Application Support/Splynek/.

      NOT entitled:
        - iCloud container access (only the MAS variant uses CloudKit,
          and only for the iPhone Companion's cellular relay).
        - JIT / unsigned-executable-memory (we don't ship a JIT).
        - Camera / mic / location (Splynek doesn't use them).
        - Apple Events (Splynek doesn't drive other apps).
    -->

    <!-- Sandbox — same posture as the existing DMG variant. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Outgoing network — HTTP downloads, torrent peers, DoH,
         appcast fetch for Sparkle, license-server activation. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Incoming network — LAN HTTP API server, Bonjour responder,
         peer-to-peer Fleet. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- User-picked file/folder access — NSOpenPanel destinations
         for downloads, license-file imports. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- ~/Downloads write access — default save location. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.files.downloads.read-write</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
